<br>
I made a short foray into the world of Camelot back in the October-November time frame....about 3 weeks after it went live as I recall. I didn't play it long, about 2 weeks (nothing specific...it just didn't seem to have the addictive qualtiy that EQ did), and I never even put in my billing info. <br>
<br>
I had a Theurgist to level 15, and I remember that the biggest issues of the time were about a 3% decrease in consignment awards, and there was a huge stink about archers being over-powered in RvR combat.<br>
<br>
So anyway, I'm just curious about what been going on in the world of DAoC? What are the big nerfs, the interesting additions, etc.? <p><h6><a href="mailto:cuchulaine_eq@hotmail.com">Geneze Angelfyre</a><br>
Templar of Tunare<br>
Veterans Legion<br>
Luclin<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32057">Magelo Profile</a></h6>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubrairwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brairwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/27/02 6:31:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Been out a while....what's changed?</span><hr size=1> You know the old saying &quot;The more things change the more they stay the same?&quot;  That pretty much sums things up. <br>
<br>
Champs Increased in PvE, reduced in RvR (big time).<br>
Archers Increased (some) in PvR, reduced (some) in RvR<br>
Wardens still broke RvR wise.<br>
<br>
Frairs did get a huge boost however.<br>
<br>
Healers stun and mezzed got nerfed.<br>
<br>
The got around to put items in most dungeons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaliciaswiftfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salicia Swiftfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>DAOC Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/28/02 12:42:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A lot has changed since release</span><hr size=1> Heres a few things added.<br>
<br>
Spell crit damage (yep, theurgists too)<br>
<br>
Spell Casting haste spells<br>
<br>
Epic zones (with flying dragons, youch)<br>
<br>
Big assassin upgrades<br>
<br>
A lot of spell changes and upgrades<br>
<br>
Visible arrows (heh)<br>
<br>
bunch of new monster models (more planned as well)<br>
<br>
a lot of itemization for zones.<br>
<br>
resist spells<br>
<br>
There is a bunch more stuff, too numerous to list.  Also worth mentioning, coming in the next patch<br>
<br>
Guild owned Keeps in the frontier, where the guards will wear the guilds emblem and guild tag under the guards name.<br>
<br>
Mid-level RVR "training" zones for levels 30 to 35 only.<br>
<br>
new spells for Cabalists to help their effectiveness<br>
<br>
and finally, scheduled for the near future but with no release date as of yet.<br>
<br>
An epic dungeon tied to the frontiers that the realms can battle for control over.  Once the realm has control, they can adventure in the dungeon.  Said dungeon is supposed to be huge, more along the lines of EQ's Old Sebillis than the cramped dungeons that DAoC currently has.<br>
<br>
Disguise for assassins that will let them trick enemies (in RVR)<br>
<br>
A "super" rvr server where RVR can happen anywhere (not just in frontiers), you can gain and lose xp from PVP and the guards are almost non-existant, requiring much more player policing for enemies.<br>
<br>
<br>
There is so much stuff being added now that its hard to keep up with it all. <p><font size=4><b>Fortuna Veldingard<br></b></font>
<i>Norse "Zerker Chick" of Nimue</i><br>
<font size=4><b>Salicia Swiftfoot<br></b></font><i>
Druid of Palomides, Retired
Ravensworn</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulilwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LilWolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/28/02 1:41:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I agree on some</span><hr size=1> I dont' think it is as addictive as EQ.<br>
<br>
I think the reason is that there isn't any broadcast channels from 1-20.  It really gets rid of the social aspect in my mind.<br>
<br>
I never minded leveling in EQ (I think downtime needed to be reduced... but another topic).  I would have great chats with people in zone.  I almost prefered to hunt in crowded zones just for the conversations.  This is also how I got into every guild that I was in.  By talking to people and getting invited. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showPrevMessage?topicID=278.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showNextMessage?topicID=278.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=3><img src=http://dev.thedruidsgrove.org/images/forum/addreplya.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.emailToFriend?topicID=278.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.threadControl?topicID=278.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=278.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=278.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option